div.div: This document illustrates the process for what we know as the Content Build, which is executed when the command yarn build:content is executed in a vets-website project. It is also executed as the "rerelease_job" during a Content Release. In this case, the commit SHA of the latest vets-website release is used to check out the source code at that time, then a Content Build is executed to rehydrate the static content of the website while leaving Webpack assets the same as was in the original release.

div.span:
The pages directory of the vagov-content repo is the the original source of content when Metalsmith is initialized.
The pages directory contains Markdown files, which was the original format for writing content in vets-website pre-CMS.
The Markdown files here are largely pages that are not of major interest to the Content Team, or pages that contain components that are not available in the CMS.
In general, a page named random/example.md would become /random/example/index.html once published to the website. However, if a page explicitly states permalink: false at the top of the file in its "front matter", then it would become /random/example.html.
Markdown files specific the name of their top-level template using a layout property. For instance, layout: page.html references the page.html layout in vets-website.

div.div:
getAllPagesViaIndividualizedGraphQlQueries
1. Sends a request for counting certain types of nodes. This is used for pagination.
2. Gets a list of GraphQL queries. This is a function instead of a static list because some queries require CMS feature flags, which are loaded async. So, if it were a static list, the CMS feature flags would not be defined.
3. Executes the queries in parallel.
4. Consolidates the response JSON of each query into a single data structure.
5. Returns the final data structure, which will be cached as a pages.json file. At this time, this data is referred to as as drupalData.

For instance, if the current build is a staging build, then instances of "https://www.va.gov/health-care/" would be replaced with "https://staging.va.gov/health-care."
